A Saudi Arabian court sentenced two
Asian men to 3,000 lashes each and five years in jail for
kidnapping a compatriot in  Riyadh ,  Arab News  reported.  The two men had taken the victim to a farm in south Riyadh,
then demanded ransom from a relative for his release, the
Jeddah-based newspaper reported, citing a police statement in
court. The paper didnâ€™t reveal their nationalities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
